examples.en: He counted seven deer in the field.
The number of cougar attacks on humans can be counted on the fingers of one hand.
The teller counted out ten $50 bills.
I was amazed at the number of plants  I counted 147.
The old fighter was counted out at the end of the third round.
The cattle have to be rounded up and counted.
He hadn't counted on the slackness of the rope.
He counted (up)on his parents to help with the expenses.
Her poetry is counted among the best-known this century.
The presence of Paula was one thing he hadn't counted on.
Today's session is counted as training, so you will get paid.
It is more than likely (=almost certain) the votes will have to be counted again.
